This paper discusses the privacy and performance limitations of TCP Fast Open (TFO) protocol and proposes a novel protocol called TCP Fast Open Privacy (FOP) to overcome these limitations. The paper focuses on network security and privacy issues, which are typically covered in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the implementation and performance of the proposed protocol, which falls under the cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new protocol design, which can be classified under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
